The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Calendar for local meets
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Calendar for local meets
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Back with a bang at the CAB after 19 months, Jagmohan Dalmiya wants to operate things in a different way.         
	Firstly, he wants to have a well-planned cricket calendar for the upcoming season so that the local leagues do not spill over to July as happened this year.         
	He (Dalmiya) wants to have a cricket calendar first A well planned one so that the local leagues are better organised and get over in time. The calendar will be designed keeping in mind Edens international and other engagements, an office bearer said.         
	It was also learnt that after every month, the functioning of the various committees and sub-committees (yet to be formed) will be reviewed.         
	It was learnt Biswarup Dey is likely to look after junior cricket along with districts and university cricket.                                                                                                                          
